Options:
  ALARMS
    -show-callstacks  display the call stacks when reporting alarms in text format (default: false)
    -show-safe-checks  show safe checks when reporting alarms in text format (default: false)
  C
    -I  add the directory to the search path for include files in C analysis
    -Wall  display compiler warnings. (default: unset)
    -additional-stubs  additional stubs file
    -c-check-float-division-by-zero  float divisions by 0 generate errors instead of infinities (default: false)
    -c-check-float-invalid-operation  invalid float operations generate errors instead of silent NaN (default: false)
    -c-check-float-overflow  float overflows generate errors (default: false)
    -c-check-overflows-with-relational  check for overflows using the relational abstract domains too (more expensive but can be more precise) (default: true)
    -c-check-unreachable-memory  check for unreachable allocated memory (default: main)
    -c-entry  name of the entry function to be analyzed (default: main)
    -c-ignore-translation-units  list of translation units ignored during linking.
    -c-init-memset-threshold  Size threshold (in bytes) for using memset to initialize memory blocks instead of a sequence of assignments (default: 50)
    -c-symbolic-args  set the number of symbolic arguments given to main (syntax: min[:max])
    -c-symbolic-args-max-size  set the maximum allocated size of all symbolic arguments (default: 18446744073709551615)
    -c-symbolic-args-min-size  set the maximum allocated size of all symbolic arguments (default: 1)
    -ccopt  pass the option to the Clang frontend
    -cell-deref-expand  maximal number of expanded cells when dereferencing a pointer (default: 1)
    -cell-smash  activate the on-demand smashing when the expansion threshold is reached
    -cell-smash-only-pointers  the on-demand smashing happens only on pointers
    -disable-parser-cache  disable the cache of the Clang parser. (default: unset)
    -error-is-builtin assume error function corresponds to the builtin (default: true)
    -library-only  allow library-only targets in the .db files (used for multilanguage analysis) (default: false)
    -make-target  binary target to analyze; used only when the Makefile builds multiple targets.
    -target-triple  target architecture to analyze, as a triple (host if left empty).
    -use-stub  list of functions for which the stub is used instead of the declaration.
    -without-libc  disable stubs of the standard C library. (default: false)
  CONFIGURATION
    -cache  size of the analysis cache (default: 5)
    -clean-cur-only  flag to apply cleaners on the current environment only
    -config  path to the configuration file to use for the analysis
    -hook  activate a hook
    -share-dir  path to the share directory
    -v  Mopsa version
    -working-dir  set the working directory, used when resolving relative paths
  COVERAGE
    -c-show-line-coverage  turn on per-line coverage reporting
  DEBUGGING
    -debug  select active debug channels. (syntax: <c1>,<c2>,...,<cn> and '_' can be used as a wildcard) (default: print)
    -engine={automatic,interactive,dap} selects analysis mode (default: automatic)
    -no-color  deactivate colors in debug messages.
    -no-warning  deactivate warning messages
  GOTO
    -goto-down  perform a down iteration after goto stabilization (default: false)
  HEAP
    -default-alloc-pol={all,range,callstack,range_callstack}  allocation policy used by default (default: range_callstack)
    -hash-heap-address   format heap addresses with their hash (default: false)
  HELP
    --help  display the list of options
    -h  display the list of options
    -help  display the list of options
    -list  list available domains/checks/hooks; if a configuration is specified, only used domains are listed
  INTERPROCEDURAL ANALYSIS
    -disable-var-renaming-recursive-call  disable renaming of local variables when detecting recursive calls
  LOOPS
    -loop-decr-it  enable decreasing iteration (default: disabled)
    -loop-full-unrolling  unroll loops without applying widening (default: false)
    -loop-full-unrolling-at  fully unroll loop at specific program location (syntax: [file.]line)
    -loop-no-cache  do not use cache for loops (default: use cache)
    -loop-unrolling  number of unrolling iterations before joining the environments (default: 1)
    -loop-unrolling-at  number of unrolling iterations at specific program location (syntax: [file.]line:unrolling)
    -widening-delay  number of iterations before applying a widening (default: 0)
  NUMERIC
    -float-rounding-mode={near,zero,up,down,rnd} rounding mode of floating-point computations. (default: near)
  OUTPUT
    -format={text,json}  selects the output format. (default: text)
    -lflow  display the last output (default: false)
    -output  redirect output to a file
    -silent  do not return a non-zero value when detecting alarms (default: unset)
    -tw  set the tab width (default: 4)
  PROFILING
    -flamegraph  path where flame graphs samples are saved
    -flamegraph-resolution={s,ms,us,ns}  resolution of the flame graph samples (default: ms)
  STUBS
    -stub-ignore-case  list of stub cases to ignore
    -stub-use-forall-loop-evaluation  use the fallback evaluation of universally quantified formulas with loops
  UNIT TESTS
    -unittest  activate unittest mode
    -unittest-filter  list of test functions (separated by comma) to analyze
